sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K737014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part composed of fusion gene between gvpC-20 and GFP mut 3.1 by using rigidity hinge which Length can achieve 41 ?? and Fad-Fad Angle is 123 ??a The fusion protein is used to detect the expression of gvpC within the cell volume.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianhe Wang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Yes,GVP comes from Planktothrix rubescens strain BC-Pla 9402.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: New Fusion Protein Systems Designed to Give Soluble Expression in Escherichia coli Gregory D. Davis,* Claude Elisee, Denton M. Newham, Roger G. Harri Received 26 January 1999; accepted 16 May 1999
